Package gui.images

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    ClassHubsPanel
    This panel represents lists of hubs, good hubs and bad hubs.
    ClassifierResultPanel
    This panel represents classification results as a pie charts for the tested classifiers.
    ClassNameAndColorPanel
    This is a simple panel that is used for displaying the color of each class.
    CodebookVectorProfilePanel
    This panel is used for displaying a visual word occurrence profile in a chart, along with its index, while estimating the utility of different visual words.
    ImageCollectionHandler
    This GUI allows the users to do some batch image processing and SIFT feature extraction via SiftWin.
    ImageHubExplorer
    This GUI was made with the intention of helping with analyzing the hubness of the data and image data in particular, in terms of the skewed distribution of implied relevance stemming from a particular choice of metric and feature representation.
    ImageManipulator
    This class implements a simple GUI for SIFT feature extraction and visualization as well as segmentation - on a single image.
    ImagePanel
    This class is an image-holding panel.
    ImagePanelWithClass
    This class is an image-holding panel that also displays the class-affiliation information as a colored frame around the image.
    ImagesDisplayPanel
    This panel is used for displaying an image dataset.
    MinMaxClustersDialog
    This dialog sets up a choice for setting the minimal and maximal numbers of clusters to use in clustering, prior to choosing the best configuration.
    QuantizedImageViewer
    This frame is used for visual word utility assessment in Image Hub Explorer.
    VerticalFlowLayout
    A vertical flow layout is similar to a flow layout but it layouts the components vertically instead of horizontally.
